nce communications ltd rcom is an indian internet access and telecommunications company headquartered in navi mumbai india it provides gsm voice g g g mobile services fixed line broadband and voice services dth depending upon the areas of operation reliance communications is the sixth largest telecom operator in india with  million subscribers as of march  established in  it is a subsidiary of reliance anil dhirubhai ambani group reliance communication it support is provided by reliance tech services and telecom network is maintained and operated by ericsson transmission towers are maintained by its subsidiary reliance infratel reliance infocomm laid the largest optic fiber cable network in the country in  to  approximately  km and touched almost all top broadband cities with the help of their franchisees  local cable operators lcos on an average  large lcos were connected to the reliance infocomm network to provide voice data and video services known as triple play on iptv platform after the split of the telecom business venture between mukesh ambani and anil ambani the telecom business was handed over to anil ambani who later christened the company as reliance communications limited in september  rcom announced that it would merge its wireless business with aircel contents  history  acquisition of mts india  merger of wireless business with aircel  network coverage  ultraband  subsidiaries  reliance digital tv ltd  reliance infratel ltd  global cloud xchange  reliance global call  references  external links historyedit reliance communications ltd was established in  the same year it launched cdma services nationwide in  reliance communications launched gsm services in the  spectrum auction reliance communications paid ₹  million for g spectrum in  circles delhi mumbai kolkata punjab rajasthan madhya pradesh west bengal himachal pradesh bihar odisha assam north east and jammu  kashmir on  may  rcom announced a price reduction of  on its g services in  reliance provided up to  mbits data rate in india with its mimo technology on  january  rcom announced its partnership with lenovo to market cobranded smartphones in india the smartphones were said to use the android operating system and have dualcore processors in  it launched cdma in rev b technology in non g circles in april  rcom informed its cdma subscribers that it would be shutting down its cdma operations and that all cdma subscribers would be migrated to gsm and lte networks the company announced that the migration had been completed in september  acquisition of mts indiaedit on  january  rcom announced that it had acquired sistema shyam teleservices limited sstl doing business as mts india in an all stock deal in which sstl received a  stake in rcom after paying off its existing debt rcom would assume the liability for installments that sstl had to pay the government from purchasing spectrum the liability amounted ₹ crore annually for  years as a result of the deal reliance acquired mts indias subscribers as well as sstls spectrum in the  mhz band the merger deal was approved by the competition commission of india cci in february  sebi cleared the deal by march and sstl shareholders approved the deal on  march by midaugust the deal was approved by tax authorities and the shareholders and creditors of rcom and sstl the merger was approved by the rajasthan high court on  september  and the bombay high court on  october  the merger is expected to be completed in mid in april rcom laid off  employees in preparation for its merger with mts and aircel merger of wireless business with airceledit on  september  rcom and maxis communications owners of aircel announced that they would merge their mobile network operations the deal is the largest consolidation in indian telecom history and will create the fourth largest mobile network operator in the country by subscribers and by revenue rcom and maxis each will hold  stake in the merged entity with equal representation on the board of directors and all committees rcom will continue to operate in the enterprise segment and data centre businesses as a standalone entity rcom announced on  march  that it had received approval for the deal from sebi bse and nse the deal was approved by the cci on  march  the shareholders of aircel and rcom approved the merger on  and  april  respectively the merger is expected to be completed by mid network coverageedit reliance communications operates in all  telecom circles of india and offers services on gsm and cdma platforms mobile services are available in the following telecom circles telecom circle g g g andhra pradesh  telangana under g partner with reliance jio assam under g partner with reliance jio bihar  jharkhand under g partner with reliance jio delhi under g partner with reliance jio gujarat under g partner with reliance jio haryana under g partner with reliance jio himachal pradesh under g partner with reliance jio jammu and kashmir under g partner with reliance jio karnataka under g partner with reliance jio kerala under g partner with reliance jio kolkata under g partner with reliance jio madhya pradesh  chhattisgarh under g partner with reliance jio maharashtra  goa under g partner with reliance jio mumbai under g partner with reliance jio northeast under g partner with reliance jio odisha under g partner with reliance jio punjab under g partner with reliance jio rajasthan under g partner with reliance jio tamil nadu under g icr with aircel under g partner with reliance jio west bengal under g partner with reliance jio uttar pradesh east under g icr with aircel under g partner with reliance jio uttar pradesh west under g icr with tata docomo under g partner with reliance jio ultrabandedit rcom launched its ultraband service offering internet speeds of up to  gbps in select locations in mumbai and navi mumbai in april  subsidiariesedit reliance telecom limited rtl operates in madhya pradesh west bengal himachal pradesh odisha bihar assam and 